The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, June 5: An Indian was killed today in a terrorist attack on the Zaranj-Delaram highway in Nimorz province of Afghanistan. He has been identified as Dev Kumar, a constable with the Indo-Tibetan Border Police.           
	Four other ITBP personnel  Ramesh Kumar, Onkar Nath, Sandeep Nath and Pradeep Singh  have been injured.           
	We strongly condemn this latest act of terrorism on a project being executed for the development of Afghanistan. Such acts will not deter us from fulfilling our humanitarian commitments, said a foreign ministry spokesperson. This is the third attack on Indians involved in the highway project in six months.                  
	Jammu (PTI): A youth has been arrested for allegedly raping a 13-year-old girl here last week, sources said on Thursday. Anil Kumar, arrested on Wednesday, is related to the girls father, who had registered a complaint with police.                  
	Chennai: The husband of MGRs adopted daughter was clubbed to death on Wednesday, allegedly because of a family feud. Vijayakumar, married to Sudha, was beaten with logs by four persons when he was returning home from office. The 55-year-old died in hospital. Hours later, Sudha filed a police complaint saying she suspected Rajendran, the husband of Latha, another adopted daughter of MGR. They were locked in a legal battle over the management of MGRs properties in the city.                   
	Ahmednagar (PTI): Forty-one people including 11 girls, who were dancing in an allegedly obscene manner, have been arrested in Maharashtra, police said on Thursday. Police raided the Antakshari Kala Kendra, owned by a retired police officers brother                  
	 New York (PTI): An American was arrested for allegedly assaulting his Sikh classmate and forcibly removing his patka in the second incident in a month of students from the community being targeted in schools. The ninth grader was suspended.                   
	Seoni (PTI): Eight pilgrims were killed and three injured when their jeep collided head-on with a truck in Madhya Pradesh on Thursday.                                                                                                                         
